  "texts": [
    "We hypothesize these rates reflect pretraining data, where authentic human self-descriptions naturally contain gendered language when referencing family members, relationships, or mentors.Financial Advisor showed only 1.8% gendered language, a 10.5-fold reduction from Classical Musician.",
    "If pretraining data drives the 11-19% rates observed in other personas, Financial Advisor's 1.8% rate plausibly reflects substantial reduction through explicit intervention.",
    "We hypothesize this pattern results from domain-specific training for both AI identity disclosure (Section 3.4) and gender-neutral language in financial advisory contexts, plausibly driven by regulatory requirements around AI disclosure and non-discrimination in financial services.The failure of this pattern to generalize suggests context-specific learning.",
    "Models appear to have learned \"use gender-neutral language as financial advisors\" rather than \"use gender-neutral language in professional contexts. \"",
    "This domain-specificity across two distinct safety dimensions of AI disclosure and gender-neutral language reinforces the paper's central finding that safety behaviors exhibit brittle, context-dependent patterns rather than principled generalization.Table 12."
  ],
